1> Best single player RPG ever is Betrayal at Krondor.<br>
<br>
 It had an awesome story, 70+ hours of gameplay, believeable characters, cutting edge graphics at the time, a great battle system and spell system, a 3D world to explore and a pretty much free roaming system where you could adventure almost anywhere on the map. Plus they had an actual writer for the story which made it all that much better. I've been hoping someone will do another Krondor like the original without overhauling the gameplay other than to update the graphics, combat system and spell system a little, unfortunately noone has done it right, sigh. <p>Cerranshaun Lightbringer <BR>
